Ah well there's only two rooms in there isn't there. Generally speaking for ease in the back kitchen now the back kitchen was small room about - oh about quarter the size of this I should im
agine and - in one corner there was a - a sink and - in the other corner there was the door and then the stairs led off from the door. Another corner was a door that led to the - front kitchen and in the other corner was the bath. Not the bath, I'm sorry,
 
the boiler. I think I've given you the general idea of the place now. In the centre was a Pembroke table - that's a round one you know, and we all sat round it - because when we first went in the house we didn't have sufficient money to pay or to buy a ga
s
 cooker and all the cooking was done on the range you see, there were two ranges, and it was quite - it was quite capable of doing it but then gas cookers came, in, people wanted to sell more gas cookers and people bought gas cookers - so we had a gas coo
ker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Would you have ever had meals in the other room?
