\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11619784\charrsid11682795 d to be a half a pound of scrags}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 
 end or half a pound of pieces. Though what they were I don't know but I always remember because I used repeat it - repeat it - repeat it going along. In fact a rather interesting story - I went for half a pound of suet once
 and with saying suet, suet, suet all the time I asked the man for half a pound of stewit and he looked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Can you think of some of your favourite meals?
