No. Not in our family. My mother used to say she'd got three - three children and reared the lot. But in those days you know people had seven and reared four. I remember funerals in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Can you recall anything that might be of interest now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 
Well I've been trying to get hold of somebody wh's seen a wake but I haven't been able to do so yet. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 For instance the clothes that people wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Oh well, they - at one time you know it was always considered absolu
tely essential that people should go in mourning - complete mourning if they could afford it. And - used to have black horses with - my father used to say that - that's a brown one dyed he'd say. And - the - when a child was buried they used to have white
 reins you know Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 But normally they'd be black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 
Normally. Yes. And - if they were very poor or it was only a child that was born - was dead - quite a lot of children died in those days you know - it was more or less understood - when - if i
t was a friend, I remember a little girl named Emma Evans dying and - we went in to see her. First time I ever seen a dead person. I think they thought we should do. We all - we were all told they went to heaven of course. And - then I remember the funera
l. Everybody so sad and I remember the - they only had one coach and the body - the coffin was carried on the knees of the people sitting in the coach. Of course they couldn't afford the hearse then you see.
