We - yes - not as - I told you about my father taking me to his sisters. And some times he used to go to another sisters - they - they're the two who came out of a convent. They never got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15361118 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 . No. The other one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15361118 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795  a Pro
testant. And - that's the one who lived in Elizabeth Street. Sometimes used to come to our house. And - very seldom and we used to put the red carpet out for them of course - my mother wanted to show that - that Protestant can do just as well as the Catho
lic you see. And - but what she didn't like again my father's sisters were rather advanced. They used to smoke. Two of them did at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Not the ones who'd been in the convent?
