Well 1918 I started as a labourer at William Crawford and Sons doing all sorts of jobs you know. Tin. More particularly in the tin room. Receiving the tins, that's what I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 How did you get the job with Crawfords?
