\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 You mean you went to Crawfords and asked if they had a vacancy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 Because you knew they were a good firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 No, because I - I'd - I'd - well I'd got the sack at the other place and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12206039 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 You didn't tell me why you got the sack.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8727438 RC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 
Oh I'll tell you if you like. He told me that you could - how he got the - how he started off you know saving money. And he gave me a pair of curtains once. He said he couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5786698\charrsid11682795 sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795 
 them so he said you can have them and I happened to sell them to a lady in - Birkenhead, Chestnut Grove, I remember it, and she gave me fifteen shillings for these curtains, and - shortly afterwards this fifteen shillings in me pocket - I'd never h
ad so much money in me life - a lady wanted a pair of shoes for a - boots for her husband. She said, exactly the same as you brought me last time. But put it on his own books, let him pay for it himself, you see. And then I was tempted. I knew the chap wh
o I used to buy the boots from. Senior Lewis's in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Seem Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and this chap if ever I wanted boots for myself he used to sell me them wholesale. So I bought these boots. He said, if ever you want any boots I'll get them wholesale. So I went and bought these
 boots wholesale - fifteen and sixpence. I took one of the bosses books and made a book out for this chap and charged him twenty-six shillings for it, repay me back two shillings a week. Well of course I was - I was serving the money out - getting a - and
 it grew and it grew you see - well it didn't grow very much. Didn't grow as quickly as I'd have liked it - to but then when I got other customers I used his book you see because I was too young to use me own. And - this went on for about }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5786698\charrsid11682795 eighteen months}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10033895\charrsid11682795  or - I never spent any of it because -
